We were born to be free, to expand our horizons by going where we have never gone before, and not to hang out in the relative comfort and safety of the nest, the known. There is a place within us that is courageous beyond our human understanding; it years to explore beyond the boundaries of daily life.

La Reserve 1785 was acquired in 1936 by Mademoiselle Henriette Reboul, renowned as a French antiques collector and a love priestess. She reputedly had numerous famous friends and lovers who all took abode in this magnificent residence, coming from all over the world. Under the magic wand of French Architects Laure Juhen and Louis Mariotti, Henriette Reboul’s residence took on a new lease of life and became a genuine touch gem, alluring beauty, and sensuality. Over the years, Laure and Louis found inspiration in countless travels, refining each drawing, finding unique pieces toiled with passion and unbridled talent. The finished work is a beautiful tribute to its original owner @lareserve1785

After weeks of sketches and iterations, I can’t believe my designs have come to life! I am launching my very own @mijaporter apparel line on @spaarkd. The first collection is inspired by summer in the city NYC/London. 
SPAARKD is a new platform founded by the bright minds behind @pangaia and it runs on an on-demand model to minimize waste. As a result, what is purchased is exactly what is produced. Everything is made of bio-based materials, eliminating microplastics from the conversations.

Kyoto is mainly famous for its hundreds of temples and shrines. In total, there are over 1,600 Buddhist temples and 400 Shinto shrines. In Japan, there are two main religions – Shinto and Buddhism. They co-exist and many Japanese follow both religions in their day to day life @visitjapanjp

Bvlgari Hotel Tokyo, which opened on April 4, 2023, is the first Bvlgari hotel in Japan, bringing contemporary Italian style and charm to the capital Tokyo. The hotel is located on the 40th to 45th floors of the Tokyo Midtown Yaesu skyscraper @bulgarihotels #bulgarihotels

Hidden amongst some 3,000 mostly uninhabited islands in the Seto Inland Sea - there lies a cluster of art Islands filled with surreal art installations, cutting edge museums, and architectural gems. Naoshima has become a global center of contemporary art filled with works from artists such as James Turell, Walter de Maria, Claude Monet and Kusama. The most extraordinary thing I have ever seen!

Japan is a very unique tourist destination and it offers many incredible experiences that you cannot find in any other part of the world. The culture of this country is an interesting blend of Eastern traditions and Western modernity that can be seen all across the nation. It is also a country with one of the oldest civilizations and a beautiful history. The stunning scenery with mountains and breathtaking views combined with the latest cutting edge architectural design. I am forever grateful for this this trip and all the inspirations I have found along the way 🇯🇵❤️🌸
📸 @iamivamic

All things “fashion we love” dump

The brand’s most iconic bag, the Di Bag, introduced in the 90’s, was immediately successful thanks to its famous clientele. Boldly reinterpreted today by Creative Director Walter Chiapponi, it embodies the perfect balance between traditional fine craftsmanship, experimentation and creativity. The Di Bag embraces a modern, genderless spirit, swapping its sharp lines for sensual suppleness and now available in a vast colour palette @tods

📸 @byholliem

A few weeks ago I had the pleasure of meeting @toryburch herself, where I shared with her that I listened to her podcast on @guy.raz 
It’s inspiring to hear how she identified a gap in the market and took the initiative to fill it, leading to the successful launch of her lifestyle brand in 2004. Overcoming personal and professional challenges shows her determination and resilience as an entrepreneur. Building a global brand with over 300 stores worldwide is a testament to her creativity, business acumen, and ability to connect with her audience. Tory has undoubtedly made a significant impact on the fashion industry and serves as an inspiration to many aspiring creatives and entrepreneurs.
